"    XLH rickets radiograph",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 282px; height: 360px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Standing anteroposterior films of both lower extremities help distinguish physiologic bowing from pathologic causes. This patient with X-linked hypophosphatemic rickets (XLH) has multiple widened physes. Osteopenia is evident in the adjacent metaphysis, which is also flared. Bowing tends to be more diffuse throughout the bone, rather than focal in the proximal tibia.",
